BFN 

  [Text] The chairman of the CSCE Minsk Group for 
Nagorno-Karabakh, Ian Eliasson, his deputy Mathias Mosberg, and 
the Russian President's envoy for settling the conflict in 
Karabakh, Vladimir Kazimirov, are expected to arrive in Baku on 
Thursday [12 May], Azerbaijan's Foreign Ministry told INTERFAX. 
  As INTERFAX learned from the State Counsellor for 
Humanitarian Issues, Gabil Guseinli, their goal is to review 
developments in the area of the Armenian-Azeri confrontation, 
and discuss further steps aimed at settling the conflict 
politically. 
  According to him, the guests will also visit Yerevan and 
Stepanakert. In Azerbaijan Kazimirov and the CSCE officials may 
inspect Azeri refugee camps, Guseinli said. 
  As a consistent supporter of a peaceful solution to the 
conflict, Guseinli stressed, Baku "welcomes the efforts of any 
countries and international organizations proclaiming their 
willingness to help in resolving the conflict and to undertake 
certain mediatory functions." Therefore Azerbaijan will welcome 
any steps suggested by the CSCE and Russia with a view to 
restoring peace in the area, the state counsellor said. 

